##Terrified, I returned to Beijing

By Wang Buyi

Source: Material Life Reference (ID: WZSHCK)

Every year during the Spring Festival, it is a big problem for me, a migrant worker from a small county on the 18th line, to return to Kyoto. From the county to the provincial capital to the capital and home again, scramble for tickets, avoid the peak, calculate the time, crowded subway, each section of the journey is enough to be exhausted. Especially this year.

This is a special Spring Festival transport year, we no longer because the huge flow of people and panic, but the virus is daunting.

My family was worried about my trip, especially after seeing a video of "the failure of Beijing West Railway Station to prevent and control the epidemic" . Video, the station exit a large number of passengers into the entrance, many people do not wear masks, temperature monitors were pushed to the side.

Fortunately, the video turned out to be fake.

They're still worried about the traffic.

On January 31st the government of Beijing said that companies should be flexible in their work arrangements, except in essential industries, and that they should postpone their start until February 10th. Logistics, O2o support industry is scheduled to fully resume production on February 10, in the Beijing Internet enterprises such as Bytedance, Meituan, jd.com, Sogou, etc. will be tentatively scheduled to resume work on February 10.

Around February 10, a large number of people are expected to return to work in Beijing.

More than 10 million people left Beijing by rail and Civil Aviation during the 14-day Spring Festival travel period. According to the booking data, the total number of railway passengers entering Beijing from February 2 to 18(the last day of the Spring Festival travel period) was 2.060,200, 714,200 air passengers travel to Beijing. In addition to the booked passengers, there will be potential visitors back to Beijing, will gradually booking back to Beijing.

Moving to Florida is an opportunity for a new virus to spread, so a return to work is thought to increase the chances of infection. I have been at home for more than 14 days, sure not infected, then, how to send themselves to Beijing in good condition, I and my family are very worried.

With all sorts of worries, on February 10, I set off from Hunan to return to Beijing. February 10 is the first day back to work, a large number of people had arrived in Beijing on February 8, February 9, wrong peak travel I did not feel big wave flow.

Another reason may be that large Internet companies, as well as large industrial enterprises with large numbers of employees, have chosen to delay the start of production. BYTEDANCE, for example, decided on February 9 that field workers should return to Beijing as soon as possible from February 12 to 16, and be quarantined for 14 days at the latest, tentatively starting on March 1. Employees who have returned to Beijing or are local to Beijing will start working online on February 3, with those who have completed 14 days of self-imposed quarantine arriving on February 10 and those who have not.

The Enterprise Returns to work in batches, has provided the possibility for my wrong peak, therefore my journey is very smooth. (here to remind the return journey, pay attention to the resumption of work time, try to stagger the peak.)

Driving all the way from the county seat to Hemerocallis Fulva airport, the only cars on the highway besides running trucks were a few private cars racing in the drizzle. Changsha city also unimpeded traffic, few vehicles. It took US less than four hours to complete the journey that normally takes more than four hours.

A section of the road in the county seat was partially closed. Passenger Transport, trains and other public transport between the county seat and the provincial capital, Changsha, have not been opened for the time being. Direct flights from our city to Beijing have been cancelled, changsha direct to Beijing high-speed rail only one trip... at home I once worried about how to return to Beijing, each section of the journey has been repeatedly considered, and asked whether the restrictions on foreign vehicles into Changsha. I ended up driving to Changsha and then flying back to Beijing, minimizing my exposure and human contact.

The expected path did not arrive, but everything was smooth.

And the flight was clear. The plane, scheduled to take off at 6 p.m. and arrive at 8:20, took off three minutes early and arrived in Beijing at forty-five. That's up from 64% in the past.

The opposite of unobstructed is quiet.

In 2019, it handled 2.997 million passengers, handled 22,000 transport trips and handled more than 80,000 passengers for Changsha Huanghua International Airport. Check-in counters were reduced and staff wore masks and gloves to prepare themselves for spraying alcohol for disinfection. The airport shops closed more than half, shop assistants are wearing masks in the shop, guarding no one cares about the shop, although the restaurant open, but the number of diners significantly reduced.

Not only at Hemerocallis FULVA's airports, airlines have slashed flights in the past week to half the volume of flights during the 2019 Spring Festival travel rush, with less than 45 per cent of passengers using the airport, compared with 90 per cent during the same period last year.

Once in Beijing Capital International Airport, there was silence. They waited in silence for their luggage and talked little. The number of buses to and from the city has been reduced to two or three, and the queues at taxi stands, which used to be so long, are now more crowded than ever.

An empty taxi zone

On the way home, after Chaoyang Joy city, only 9:00, once the noise, bright lights joy city has been lights out. Its business hours have been adjusted to 11:00 to 18:00 and a cloud shopping service has been launched. And earlier, I had seen in Wechat group Joy City cloud sea dishes selling fruit and vegetables news, the catering industry can be expected to be affected.

The streets are quiet. The driver took one look at the empty bus beside him and said to me, "look, there's nobody here. "

Chaoyang Joy city with lights out and doors closed

"Menu" of Yunhai dishes (wechat group photo)

Another key word for returning to Beijing is "isolation" .

I am reassured by the rigour of the procedure in public places.

From Hemerocallis Fulva airport to Beijing Capital International Airport, there are four stages to a body temperature test: entering an airport temperature gun, going through security, infrared testing, getting on an airplane temperature gun, getting off an airplane, infrared testing, if you choose the subway to go home, then you have to go through an infrared scan before you get on the train. When you get to the compound, the security guard will be waiting for you with a thermometer in his hand.

If there are fever patients, it is almost impossible to slip through the net.

The public's self-awareness is also reassuring. Because the flow of people is small, in the airport lobby, passengers wearing masks are automatically segregated to sit, no one gathered together. Others wear raincoats for protection.

And the quarantine on the plane is in place. While everyone had to wear masks, planes were not sold out, and tickets were distributed to separate passengers. The plane I was on was a row of six seats, three on each side, with a corridor in the middle, a seat or corridor between people.

This is what the Ministry of Transport of the People's Republic of China calls for: Controlling the occupancy rate of vehicles, providing space for passengers to sit in separate, scattered seats, and at the rear of the vehicle, reserve a part of the space as a temporary isolated area in case of emergency, to avoid cross-infection. Long-distance international flights must eat, to take the seat next to the passengers eat in batches, to avoid cross-infection.

In addition, personal protection is essential.

I have two masks for myself, two layers for when I get on the plane (because it's enclosed space) , and surgical disposable gloves to reduce hand contact. Bring Your Own Cup, bought a bucket of instant noodles, do not eat anything outside. On the plane, the meal was changed from hot food to snacks and mineral water, but I still didn't eat it. From what I can tell, most of the passengers are choosing not to eat.

The aircraft broadcast the prompt: Commercial Aircraft Cabin 2-3 minutes to replace the air, aircraft ventilation system to reduce the possibility of the spread of the virus. It made me, wearing two layers of face masks, feel like my efforts were not in vain.

When I got off the plane, I took a cab home to avoid public contact. In the car, see such a scene: a family of three people with a child, was refused taxi driver, said that can not sit.

After the driver explained, I understand: This period, passengers are not allowed to sit in the passenger, is responsible for the passengers, is also responsible for the driver.

The master said: We go out every day, close the car, the car has to be disinfected, there are passengers in the car, the front and rear windows have to open a fan, to maintain ventilation.

I nodded.

The community has also set up a disinfection area at the door, after measuring the body temperature, I filled out the registration card to return to Beijing, stating where to come from, flight number, there are no symptoms, and so on. I filled this out on the plane, too.

When I got home, I put all my clothes on the balcony to dry, took out a 56-degree red star Erguotou I had bought in Beijing Capital International Airport, and began disinfecting my suitcase and myself (because alcohol was not available) .

The fight against the plague is a battle of rivals in the shadows. We must do every detail in order to defeat this invisible enemy.
